This is just a quick script I wrote to wrap the s3cmd sync command
in a script I could use with a configuration file, rather than doing
each directory line by line.

I'm not thrilled with the XML format, and would rather use an Apache
style config, or something generally more legible.

Example XML format of s3cmd_backup.conf

<s3cmd_backup>
	<config>
		<s3cmd> /usr/bin/trickle -u 64 /usr/bin/s3cmd </s3cmd>
		<s3_config_file> /home/fred/.s3cfg </s3_config_file>
		<params> -rH --no-check-md5 --exclude ".DS_Store" </params>
		<email_subject> s3 Backup - My Backup </email_subject>
		<email_address> fred@example.com </email_address>
	</config>
	<backup>
		<source> /media/Files </source>
		<destination> s3://my_bucket/dir </destination>
		<directory>
			<path> files/Videos </path>
		</directory>
		<directory>
			<path> files/Music </path>
			<params> --exclude '*.wav' </params>
		</directory>
	</backup>
	<backup>
	...
	</backup>
	<backup>
	...
	</backup>
</s3cmd_backup>

